#[global] Unset Universe Checking.

(***********************************************************************************

 Monads can be composed if we have a distributive law between them

 This results holds for monads in arbitrary bicategories. For monads of categories,
 this was already proved in Monads.Derivative.v (`monad_comp`)

 ***********************************************************************************)

Local Open Scope cat.

Section ComposeMonad.
  Context {B : bicat}
          {x : B}
          (dm‚ÇÅ dm‚ÇÇ : disp_mnd B x)
          (Œ± : distr_law dm‚ÇÅ dm‚ÇÇ).

  Let m‚ÇÅ : mnd B := x ,, dm‚ÇÅ.
  Let m‚ÇÇ : mnd B := x ,, dm‚ÇÇ.

  Let f : x --> x := endo_of_mnd m‚ÇÅ.
  Let g : x --> x := endo_of_mnd m‚ÇÇ.

  Let Œ∑‚ÇÅ : id‚ÇÅ _ ==> f := unit_of_mnd m‚ÇÅ.
  Let Œ∑‚ÇÇ : id‚ÇÅ _ ==> g := unit_of_mnd m‚ÇÇ.

  Let Œº‚ÇÅ : f ¬∑ f ==> f := mult_of_mnd m‚ÇÅ.
  Let Œº‚ÇÇ : g ¬∑ g ==> g := mult_of_mnd m‚ÇÇ.

  Let Œ∑c : id‚ÇÅ x ==> f ¬∑ g
    := linvunitor _ ‚Ä¢ (Œ∑‚ÇÅ ‚ñπ _) ‚Ä¢ (_ ‚óÉ Œ∑‚ÇÇ).

  Let Œºc
    : f ¬∑ g ¬∑ (f ¬∑ g) ==> f ¬∑ g
    := rassociator _ _ _
       ‚Ä¢ (f ‚óÉ lassociator _ _ _)
       ‚Ä¢ (f ‚óÉ (Œ± ‚ñπ g))
       ‚Ä¢ (f ‚óÉ rassociator _ _ _)
       ‚Ä¢ lassociator _ _ _
       ‚Ä¢ (Œº‚ÇÅ ‚ñπ _)
       ‚Ä¢ (_ ‚óÉ Œº‚ÇÇ).

Œ±: distr_law dm‚ÇÅ dm‚ÇÇ

m‚ÇÇ:= x,, dm‚ÇÇ: mnd B
f:= endo_of_mnd m‚ÇÅ: B ‚ü¶ x, x ‚üß
g:= endo_of_mnd m‚ÇÇ: B ‚ü¶ x, x ‚üß

Œ∑‚ÇÇ:= unit_of_mnd m‚ÇÇ: id‚ÇÅ x ==> g
Œº‚ÇÅ:= mult_of_mnd m‚ÇÅ: f ¬∑ f ==> f
Œº‚ÇÇ:= mult_of_mnd m‚ÇÇ: g ¬∑ g ==> g
Œ∑c:= (linvunitor (id‚ÇÅ x) ‚Ä¢ (Œ∑‚ÇÅ ‚ñπ id‚ÇÅ x)) ‚Ä¢ (f ‚óÉ Œ∑‚ÇÇ): id‚ÇÅ x ==> f ¬∑ g
Œºc:= (((((rassociator f (endo_of_mnd (x,, dm‚ÇÇ))
       (endo_of_mnd (x,, dm‚ÇÅ) ¬∑ g)
     ‚Ä¢ (f
        ‚óÉ lassociator (endo_of_mnd (x,, dm‚ÇÇ))
            (endo_of_mnd (x,, dm‚ÇÅ)) g))
    ‚Ä¢ (f ‚óÉ (Œ± ‚ñπ g)))
   ‚Ä¢ (f
      ‚óÉ rassociator (endo_of_mnd (x,, dm‚ÇÅ))
          (endo_of_mnd (x,, dm‚ÇÇ)) g))
  ‚Ä¢ lassociator f (endo_of_mnd (x,, dm‚ÇÅ))
      (endo_of_mnd (x,, dm‚ÇÇ) ¬∑ g))
 ‚Ä¢ (Œº‚ÇÅ ‚ñπ endo_of_mnd (x,, dm‚ÇÇ) ¬∑ g)) ‚Ä¢ (f ‚óÉ Œº‚ÇÇ): f ¬∑ g ¬∑ (f ¬∑ g) ==> f ¬∑ g
(linvunitor (f ¬∑ g) ‚Ä¢ (Œ∑c ‚ñπ f ¬∑ g)) ‚Ä¢ Œºc = id‚ÇÇ (f ¬∑ g)
